(In reply to Graham Perrin from comment #1)

I did not know about the existence of subprojects. While it would be logical to make status-reviewers a subproject of docs, I would refrain from doing that because:

- in the same link you gave us Graham, I read, after scrolling up a bit, that the "Subprojects and Milestones" feature is "only partially implemented";

- I do not see any advantage in having status-reviewers being a subproject of docs. If you see any, please share;

- we do not have many groups in Phabricator and I think we have zero subgroups. And things seem to work well. Maybe subgroups are a feature for Phabricator instances that are more complex from our own, maybe it is also more useful for large business companies than for open source projects.

So I would keep it simple at least for now and create both the new projects as normal projects. I guess we can always turn one or both of them into subprojects in the future if we want.
